{"id":53,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":53,"title":"Chapter 49: Mormon and His Teachings","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 49","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 49"],["h1","Mormon and His Teachings"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p3"},"Many years after Jesus Christ visited the Nephites, a small group of people left the Church and called themselves Lamanites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.20"},"4 Nephi 1:20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p5"},"Eventually almost all the people became wicked, both Nephites and Lamanites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.45"},"4 Nephi 1:45"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p7"},"A righteous man, Ammaron, had the sacred records. The Holy Ghost told him to hide them so they would be safe."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.48-49"},"4 Nephi 1:48–49"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p9"},"Ammaron told Mormon, a 10-year-old boy, where the records were hidden. Ammaron knew he could trust Mormon."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.2-3"},"Mormon 1:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p11"},"When he was 24, Mormon was to get the plates of Nephi and write on them about his people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.3-4"},"Mormon 1:3–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p13"},"When Mormon was 11, a war started between the Nephites and Lamanites. The Nephites won, and there was peace again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.6,8-12"},"Mormon 1:6, 8–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p15"},"But the Nephites were so wicked that the Lord took away the three disciples, which ended the miracles and healings. The Holy Ghost no longer guided the people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.13-14"},"Mormon 1:13–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p17"},"When Mormon was 15, Jesus Christ visited him. Mormon learned more about the Savior and his goodness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.15"},"Mormon 1:15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p19"},"Mormon wanted to preach to the people, but Jesus told him not to because the people were too wicked. Their hearts were set against God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/1.16-17"},"Mormon 1:16–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p21"},"Soon another war began. Mormon was large and strong, and the Nephites chose him to lead their army."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/2.1"},"Mormon 2:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p23"},"The Nephites fought the Lamanites for many years. Mormon tried to encourage his people to fight for their families and homes."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/2.23"},"Mormon 2:23"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p25"},"The Nephites had become so wicked, though, that the Lord would not help them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/2.26"},"Mormon 2:26"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p27"},"Mormon told the Nephites they would be spared only if they repented and were baptized. But the people refused."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/3.2-3"},"Mormon 3:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p29"},"They bragged about their strength, saying they would kill all the Lamanites. Because of the Nephites’ wickedness, Mormon refused to lead them any longer."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/3.9-11"},"Mormon 3:9–11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p31"},"The Lamanites began defeating the Nephites in every battle. Mormon decided to lead the Nephite armies again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/4.18"},"Mormon 4:18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/5.1"},"Mormon 5:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p33"},"He knew the wicked Nephites would not win the war. They did not repent or pray for the help they needed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/5.2"},"Mormon 5:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p35"},"Mormon took all the records from the hill where Ammaron had hidden them and wrote to the people who would one day read the record."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/4.23"},"Mormon 4:23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/5.9,12"},"Mormon 5:9, 12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_18.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p37"},"He wanted everyone, including the Jews, to know about Jesus Christ, to repent and be baptized, and to live the gospel and be blessed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p38"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/5.14"},"Mormon 5:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/7.8,10"},"Mormon 7:8, 10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f19"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_19.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p39"},"The Spirit inspired Mormon to put the small plates of Nephi, which contained the prophecies of Christ’s coming, with the plates of Mormon."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p40"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/w-of-m/1.3-7"},"Words of Mormon 1:3–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f20"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_20.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p41"},"Mormon led the Nephites to the land of Cumorah, where they got ready to fight the Lamanites again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p42"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/6.4"},"Mormon 6:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_21.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p43"},"Mormon was getting old. He knew this would be the last battle. He did not want the Lamanites to find the sacred records and destroy them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/6.6"},"Mormon 6:6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_22.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p45","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p45"},"So he gave the plates of Mormon to his son, Moroni, and hid the rest of the plates in the Hill Cumorah."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p46","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p46"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/6.6"},"Mormon 6:6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f23"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_23.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p47"},"The Lamanites attacked and killed all but 24 Nephites. Mormon had been wounded."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p48"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/6.8-11"},"Mormon 6:8–11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f24"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_24.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p49","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p49"},"Mormon was sad that so many Nephites had died, but he knew they had died because they had rejected Jesus."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p50","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p50"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/6.16-18"},"Mormon 6:16–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f25"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_25.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p51","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p51"},"Mormon had tried to teach the Nephites the truth. He had told them how important it was to have faith in Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p52","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p52"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.1,33,38"},"Moroni 7:1, 33, 38"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f26"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_26.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p53"},"He had tried to teach them to have hope through Jesus Christ’s Atonement and to have charity, which is the pure love of Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p54","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p54"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.40-41,47"},"Moroni 7:40–41, 47"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f27"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_27.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p55"},"And Mormon had written letters to his son, Moroni, who had also taught the gospel to the Nephites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p56","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p56"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/8.1-2"},"Moroni 8:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f28"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_28.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p57"},"Mormon wrote about the terrible wickedness of the Nephites. He told Moroni to stay faithful in Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p58","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p58"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/9.1,20,25"},"Moroni 9:1, 20, 25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.f29"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_053_29.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p59","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p59"},"The Lamanites killed Mormon and all the Nephites but Moroni, who finished writing the records."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p60","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-49-mormon-and-his-teachings.p60"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/8.2-3"},"Mormon 8:2–3"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
